{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784240234107180506,"compiled_state":{"alias":"classless-splintery-noctule","assignee":"","attestations":{"plan-review":{"algorithm":"sshsig","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","envelope":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.opcert.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","head_sha":"ba2fb1dd4fd2cfb3c464cecbb17b66854f446a8b","key_id":null,"kind":"plan-review","manifest":["plan-review: PASS","ticket: 1a51-b170-5168-46d2","material: 901cc01f15f1e36a","model: claude-sonnet-4-6","runner: pydantic_ai","blocking: 0","advisory: 6","rebar-version: 0.8.0 (ba2fb1dd4)","regver: b293b9a55de591cc","verified-at-sha:6b25dbead186639a436b1d5faf7cb03e99001efc","dep 9a229c6a1b259a9d6f8f0c59b1f8949ac4e56c26c7fbaf1027202244ad046fc6 src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py","dep 16fc7a7f582ba05918c913c82914018ab57f7db24f78682252f6b7f06c891cff src/rebar/graph/_links.py","dep e91bc52dcf7a7b1bfc7f2c9fb5bedc1801a882b88a2622cb78e92939e072bd54 src/rebar/opcert_service/jobs.py","dep 6b1a5b7e0ca1b806e5003ea02c8302d3c58cbfe6132f23980a2354081d9a9b72 src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py"],"material_fingerprint":"901cc01f15f1e36a","merged_log_commit":"6b25dbead186639a436b1d5faf7cb03e99001efc","principal":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","signature":null,"signed_at":1784239254382513000}},"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":4,"unsigned":8},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"645f5c3bc563edf8f78d60b0d35965cf0a44a294068df8e80a2cbcb2e9edc99e","event_uuid":"99ef9731-082f-41ae-8187-6e72c28aec02","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784238783640158001-99ef9731-082f-41ae-8187-6e72c28aec02"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"b1520e36b0a9267e8d45adf82d3a38a57b0751028d010c1f0b95fa1d9310e470","event_uuid":"de267855-2431-40f8-b03d-28c8ac729641","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784239254382825001-de267855-2431-40f8-b03d-28c8ac729641"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"830009c762b6c5bd46fe17d8e555496a6df4dfe46b32076309fd87649dd5d977","event_uuid":"1fcd41bd-9ec3-49e5-bea9-f7d099506a52","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784239485909174001-1fcd41bd-9ec3-49e5-bea9-f7d099506a52"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"557b86b4dac704a49ebcfa090306fd58b827c1bb9722e2a4af677d49c92b2214","event_uuid":"1bcb9c8c-2903-4a7c-9d1e-c06a6add221a","position":{"commit_sha":null,"position":"1784240234107180505-1bcb9c8c-2903-4a7c-9d1e-c06a6add221a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-211_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"e533bbc2-be02-4c77-890b-73fde9abf109","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"## Gerrit-side ticket-store writer classification (1a51 / canary 1787)\n\nEvery Gerrit-side operation that could touch the ticket store, classified with file:line evidence.\n\n| Operation | Bucket | Evidence |\n|---|---|---|\n| opcert-service gate jobs (plan-review, completion-verifier) | **A — NON-WRITING** | `opcert_service/jobs.py:11-12` docstring \"The server never pushes… runs with REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off\"; enforced `jobs.py:196-208` (`_sync_push_off`); workspace discarded `jobs.py:97-99`; `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:168-169` \"STORE-READ-ONLY\" `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH: \"off\"`. Even a gate SIGNATURE append lands only in the discarded clone. |\n| review-bot code_review artifact (`create_ticket(\"code_review\")` + `REVIEW_RESULT`) | **B — GATE-EXEMPT** | `review_bot/voter.py:241-251`; `llm/code_review/sidecar.py:26,143`. `code_review` ∈ `_GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES` at `_commands/verify_authorship.py:125`. |\n| review-bot reciprocal `relates_to` LINK onto the trailer-cited **work** ticket | **C — IN-SCOPE WRITER** | `voter.py:278` `rebar.link(artifact_id, resolved, \"relates_to\")` where `resolved` is a real work ticket; `graph/_links.py:264-267` writes reciprocal LINK into the target work-ticket dir → `_seam.append_event(work_ticket, \"LINK\", …)`; pushed (`docker-compose.yml:93` `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH: \"always\"`). Non-exempt ticket type → gate collects the LINK event. |\n| review-bot on-box backfill reconciler (`reconcile_loop`) | same as B + C | `review_bot/reconcile.py:223` re-invokes voter; launched `review_bot/app.py:101`. Gerrit-vote backfiller (NOT a Jira reconciler). |\n| autodeploy timer | **A — no store touch** | ADR-0026; `infra/scripts/autodeploy.sh` has no create_ticket/append_event. |\n| auto-lander | **RETIRED — not deployed** | ADR-0047 (Accepted 2026-07-13); `infra/gerrit/project.config:53`. Its former bundled ticket-store write was removed as scope-creep. |\n| Jira→rebar reconcile-bridge (contrast) | IN-SCOPE but **GitHub-side, not Gerrit-side** | `.github/workflows/reconcile-bridge.yml:62` `runs-on: ubuntu-latest`; signs via `REBAR_BOT_SIGNING_KEY`. This is story 4dc0's surface, not Gerrit-side. |\n\n**In-scope Gerrit-side writer: YES** — the rebar review-bot's reciprocal `relates_to` LINK on the trailer-cited work ticket (`voter.py:278` → `graph/_links.py:264-267`), and its on-box backfill reconciler which drives the same voter.\n\n**Already provisioned to sign:** `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh:98-124` materializes SSM `/rebar/prod/rebar-bot-signing-key` to a 0600 file and exports `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`; the write seam (`_seam.py:294-315`) signs when a resolvable author_id + signing_key are present. So the review-bot signs its LINK writes as identity 594c (Rebar Bot), whose registered pubkey matches that key.\n\n**Confirmed unaffected by enforcement:** opcert-service (non-writing, never gated) and the review-bot's code_review artifacts (gate-exempt) are never rejected when require_authenticated=true.\n\n**Remaining canary-1787 validation:** confirm on the deployed Gerrit VM that the review-bot actually emits a *signed, verified* LINK event (the SSM key was populated 2026-07-14; needs a post-that-boot run to prove it).\n\n---\nAC1 satisfied (classification above, with file/line evidence). AC3 satisfied: opcert-service (REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off, never pushes) and the review-bot code_review artifacts (gate-exempt via _GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES) are structurally never rejected under require_authenticated=true. AC2/AC4 (canary 1787 — the in-scope review-bot relates_to LINK produces a signed+verified event) will be confirmed by driving the deployed review-bot with the epic's own Gerrit change (8d91 test push), then recorded here.","timestamp":1784239485909174001}],"created_at":1784226822054405001,"deps":[],"description":"## Why\n\nEnabling `identity.require_authenticated` must break nothing on the Gerrit side. Not every\nGerrit-side service writes **in-scope** ticket events, so this story **classifies** them\n(with file/line evidence) rather than blanket-signing everything, and confirms the one in-scope\nwriter actually signs on the deployed VM (finishing canary 1787, which was force-closed\n\"pending post-deploy run\").\n\n## What — enumerate and classify every Gerrit-side store operation\n\nClassification (verified against the code):\n\n- **opcert-service → NON-WRITING.** `src/rebar/opcert_service/jobs.py:11-12` (\"The server never\n  pushes… runs with `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`\"), enforced at `jobs.py:196-208` (`_sync_push_off`),\n  workspace discarded `jobs.py:97-99`; `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml:168-169`\n  (\"STORE-READ-ONLY\" / `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH: \"off\"`). Never places an event on the shared store.\n- **review-bot `code_review` artifact → GATE-EXEMPT.** `src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py:241-251`\n  (`create_ticket(\"code_review\", …)`) + `llm/code_review/sidecar.py:26,143`\n  (`REVIEW_RESULT`); `code_review ∈ _GATE_EXEMPT_TYPES` at\n  `src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py:125`.\n- **review-bot reciprocal `relates_to` LINK on the trailer-cited work ticket → IN-SCOPE\n  WRITER.** `voter.py:278` `rebar.link(artifact_id, resolved, \"relates_to\")` where `resolved`\n  is a real work ticket; `graph/_links.py:264-267` writes a reciprocal LINK event into the\n  work-ticket dir → `_seam.append_event(work_ticket, \"LINK\", …)`; pushed\n  (`docker-compose.yml:93` `REBAR_SYNC_PUSH: \"always\"`). The work ticket is non-exempt, so the\n  gate collects this LINK event. Its on-box backfill reconciler (`review_bot/reconcile.py:223`,\n  launched `app.py:101`) drives the same voter. (This LINK-write path **refines** the earlier\n  \"review-bot writes only the exempt `code_review` type\" assessment — the reciprocal\n  `relates_to` back-link onto the non-exempt work ticket was not accounted for there; the code\n  evidence above is authoritative, and is why this story confirms the bot signs rather than\n  treating it as fully exempt.)\n- **auto-lander → RETIRED** (ADR-0047; `infra/gerrit/project.config:53`), not deployed.\n- (For contrast: the Jira→rebar reconciler is a GitHub-side writer — `reconcile-bridge.yml`,\n  `runs-on: ubuntu-latest` — covered by story 4dc0, NOT Gerrit-side.)\n\n**Already provisioned to sign:** `infra/scripts/fetch-secrets.sh:98-124` materializes SSM\n`/rebar/prod/rebar-bot-signing-key` to a `0600` file and exports `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`;\nthe write seam (`_seam.py:294-315`) signs when a resolvable `author_id` (594c, via the bot git\nemail) + a `signing_key` are present. So the review-bot is equipped to sign its LINK writes as\nidentity `594c`.\n\n## Confirming canary 1787 (the in-scope path signs on the deployed VM)\n\nThe in-scope writer is exercised naturally by pushing a change through Gerrit: the deployed\nreview-bot reviews the change and emits a reciprocal `relates_to` LINK onto the change's\n`rebar-ticket:` work ticket, authored by `594c`. Confirm that LINK event is **signed +\nverified** — that is the deployed-VM proof. (Fallback: inspect the running review-bot container\non the VM via AWS SSM to confirm the key is materialized and `REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY` is\nset.)\n\n## Scope\n\nGerrit-side operations only: classification + verification. Provisioning only if an in-scope\nwriter is found **unsigned** (it is already provisioned). No enforcement flip here (8d39). No\ntracked repo-file change (empty `file_impact` is correct); the classification + canary evidence\nare recorded as comments on this ticket.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] **Every Gerrit-side store operation is enumerated and classified** non-writing /\n      gate-exempt / in-scope-writer, with file/line evidence, recorded on this ticket (the\n      table above).\n- [ ] **The in-scope Gerrit-side writer produces a signed, verified event.** Capture the\n      tickets-branch HEAD before driving the review-bot: `C=$(git -C .tickets-tracker rev-parse HEAD)`.\n      After a Gerrit change makes the deployed review-bot emit a reciprocal `relates_to` LINK on\n      its `rebar-ticket:` work ticket, confirm **both**: (a) a new LINK event authored by `594c`\n      was introduced on that work ticket after `C` — evidenced by the work ticket's\n      `rebar show <t> | jq '.authorship.signed'` increasing, recorded as the work-ticket id +\n      tickets commit (proves non-vacuous); and (b)\n      `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since \"$C\"` exits 0 (every event\n      introduced since `C`, including the LINK, verifies — had the bot LINK been unsigned it\n      would exit non-zero). Record `C`, the change URL, and the work-ticket id on this ticket.\n- [ ] **Confirmed unaffected by enforcement:** the opcert-service (`REBAR_SYNC_PUSH=off`, never\n      pushes) and the review-bot `code_review` artifacts (gate-exempt) are not rejected when\n      `require_authenticated=true` — established by the classification evidence above.\n- [ ] [operator-attested] Canary 1787 is completed for the in-scope path: the deployed\n      review-bot's reciprocal `relates_to` LINK produces an actual **signed, verified** event.\n      A materialized key is **not** sufficient — it does not prove the bot signs, and could mask\n      a signing malfunction. Required evidence recorded on this ticket: the boundary `C` and\n      work-ticket id from AC2, the `rebar verify-identity --all --require-authenticated --since \"$C\"`\n      exit-0 result (confirming the LINK verifies), and a timestamp. Obtain it by driving the\n      deployed review-bot with a real Gerrit change — this\n      epic's 8d91/8d39 changes naturally produce a review-bot LINK on their work ticket; if none\n      is in flight, push a synthetic change. A container/SSM inspection\n      (`aws ssm start-session … docker exec … env | grep REBAR_IDENTITY_SIGNING_KEY`) may be\n      recorded as *supplementary* diagnostic context only, never as a substitute for the signed\n      event.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/opcert_service/jobs.py","reason":"opcert-service non-writing classification"},{"path":"src/rebar/review_bot/voter.py","reason":"review-bot in-scope relates_to LINK writer"},{"path":"src/rebar/graph/_links.py","reason":"reciprocal LINK write path"},{"path":"src/rebar/_commands/verify_authorship.py","reason":"gate-exempt types + gate scope"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","dc09-6565-cf85-4aea"]],"parent_id":"dc09-6565-cf85-4aea","parent_status_uuid":"8763f798-2024-4bdd-b01e-a5a7f5b2afe0","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"1a51-b170-5168-46d2","ticket_type":"story","title":"Confirm Gerrit-side services sign ticket writes on the deployed VM (finish canary 1787)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["429251cb-f18a-438b-899a-38f2da9d4b26","cdb1700c-1819-4024-a303-ece06e0961c0","e77012ff-e2a3-4dd9-b93c-6fd1d6d67f81","3d856efe-3daf-4e73-8b2c-17b5b76b4050","0ac197f8-5422-44c0-b9a9-4a5895d13d58","4c7235cc-3ca9-4c01-a30b-50894f82427f","99ef9731-082f-41ae-8187-6e72c28aec02","de267855-2431-40f8-b03d-28c8ac729641","8763f798-2024-4bdd-b01e-a5a7f5b2afe0","cf85c717-09ca-4d27-8e32-a254f72998dc","1fcd41bd-9ec3-49e5-bea9-f7d099506a52","1bcb9c8c-2903-4a7c-9d1e-c06a6add221a"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784240234107180506,"uuid":"9dfd9dd3-b774-4014-aef1-21c8d5737cd5"}